<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN"
	 "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
	  xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
	  xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal">
	<head>
		<meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" />
		<title>Welcome To NextThought</title>
		<style metal:use-macro="macro:style">
		</style>
	</head>
	<body>
		<div metal:use-macro="macro:header">
		</div>

		<p>Dear <span tal:content="options/informal_username" class="realname tterm">John</span>,</p>

		<p>
			Thank you for signing up for
		&ldquo;<span tal:content="options/course/Title | default">my
		course</span>,&rdquo; an open version of a popular course in the
		<span tal:content="options/course/ProviderDepartmentTitle | default">Department
			of Classics and Letters</span>.
		</p>

		<p>
			You are about to embark on a one-of-a-kind learning
			experience through <a href="https://nextthought.com"
				tal:attributes="href request/application_url"
				tal:content="options/brand">Nextthought</a>.
			More importantly, you are joining a true learning
			community built to connect, engage, and inspire all who
			wish to learn.
		</p>

		<!-- Course in progress -->
		<p tal:condition="python: not options['course_archived'] and not options['course_preview']">
			The course is currently in progress. You are welcome to join our
			learning community and to experience the lectures and discussions on
			 <a href="https://nextthought.com"
				tal:attributes="href request/application_url"
				tal:content="options/brand">Nextthought</a>.
		</p>

		<!-- Course archived -->
		<p tal:condition="options/course_archived">
			Although the course has already formally concluded, you still have access to
			all course materials. These materials will be available to you indefinitely,
			as long as you are enrolled in the course. Please note, however, that this
			course is no longer monitored by the professor. You are welcome to join our
			learning community and to experience the lectures and discussions on
			<span tal:content="options/brand">NextThought</span>.
		</p>

		<p>
			Feel free to spread the word around about the course by forwarding
			this email or sharing about it through social media. Encourage your
			friends to join, add them as a friend, and then form a study group on
			the platform.
		</p>

		<!-- For credit url if it exists and the class is not yet started. -->
		<p tal:condition="python: options['for_credit_url'] and options['course_preview']">
			If you are a current <span tal:content="options/site_alias"></span> student, you have the
			option to enroll in this course for credit. Enroll at
			<a href="" tal:attributes="href python: 'https://' + options['for_credit_url']" tal:content="options/for_credit_url">link</a>
			with the corresponding course number:
			<span class="coursenumber"
				  tal:content="options/course/ProviderUniqueID">CLC 3403</span>.
		</p>

		<p tal:condition="options/course_preview">
			Expect more information soon as we get closer to the
			course start date, <span tal:content="options/course_start_date | default">January 13, 2014</span>.
		</p>

		<p>
			I look forward to seeing you in our community!
		</p>

		<p>
			All the Best,
			<br />
			<br />
			<span tal:content="structure options/instructors_html_signature">
				Dr. Kyle Harper<br />
				Associate Professor of Classics<br />
			</span>
			<br />
			<br />
		</p>

		<div id="logo-bar nti">
			<img src="http://d2ixlfeu83tci.cloudfront.net/images/email_logo.png" width="177" height="25" alt="NextThought Logo" />
		</div>

		<p class="footer" style="font-size: smaller">
			If you feel this email was sent in error, or this account was created
			without your consent, you may email
			<a href="mailto:support@nextthought.com"
				tal:attributes="href options/support_email"
				tal:content="options/support_email">support@nextthought.com</a>.
		</p>


	</body>
</html>
